'''''Pawn Stars Australia''''' is the Australian adaption of the [[Pawn Stars|American series of the same name]]. It premiered on 21 July 2015 on [[A&E Australia|A&E]].<ref name="series details">{{cite news|last1=Hansen|first1=Nick|title=Bondi's Happy Hockers in Pawn Stars Australian spin-off|url=http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/newslocal/city-east/bondis-happy-hockers-in-pawn-stars-australian-spin-off/story-fngr8h22-1227444676066|accessdate=20 July 2015|work=Wentworth Courier|date=17 July 2015}}</ref> The Australian version is the third international spin-off after [[Pawn Stars UK]] and Pawn Stars South Africa.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hogan|first1=Matthew|title=Sydney trio into hardcore pawn|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305135237/https://au.news.yahoo.com/thewest/wa/a/28827861/sydney-trio-into-hardcore-pawn/|accessdate=20 July 2015|work=[[The West Australian]]|date=16 July 2015}}</ref>

The series stars brothers Aaron and Ben Senes along with their childhood mate Shanon Folden, who own the well-known chain of pawn stores called ''Happy Hockers'' in [[Sydney]].<ref name="ref1">{{cite news|last1=Blundell|first1=Graeme|title=Reality TV show Pawn Stars Australia is a big deal|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/arts/review/reality-tv-show-pawn-stars-australia-is-a-big-deal/story-fn9n8gph-1227435498997|accessdate=20 July 2015|work=[[The Australian]]|date=11 July 2015}}</ref> 

The series is directed by Martin Baker and produced by Leftfield Pictures, the same company that produces the American original.<ref name="ref1"/>

The complete first season DVD was scheduled to be released on 5 October 2016.

==Development and production==
In April 2014 it was reported that a local adaption of ''Pawn Stars'' was in the works, with filming starting at Sydney's ''Happy Hockers'' which would last 9 weeks. It was believed an official announcement of a late 2014 premiere on A&E would come in the following days.<ref>{{cite news|last=Auerbach|first=Taylor|title=The Pawn Stars of Bondi Beach: Hit American hock show hits Australia starring brothers 'Baz and Shaz'|newspaper=Daily Mail Australia|date=4 April 2014|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2596556/Aussie-Pawn-Stars-coming-Hit-American-hock-filming-Australian-spinoff-Bondi-Beach-pawn-shop.html|accessdate=20 July 2015}}</ref> However, it wasn't until August 2014 that the series had officially been commissioned, and that Leftfield Pictures (the company behind ''Pawn Stars U.S.'') were officially confirmed as the producers of the local adaption. It was also stated that the series would air in 2015, rather than in 2014 as previously rumoured.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|title=Pawn Stars Australia coming to A&E|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2014/08/pawn-stars-australia-coming-to-ae.html|accessdate=22 July 2015|date=6 August 2014}}</ref> In June 2015 it was announced the series would officially star brothers Aaron and Ben Senes and best friend Shanon Folden and would premiere on 21 July 2015.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|title=Airdate: Pawn Stars Australia|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/06/airdate-pawn-stars-australia.html|accessdate=22 July 2015|date=30 June 2015}}</ref>

The Senes brother said they agreed to do the reality series to help the public know about the pawn industry, which they said is misunderstood. "People can see it's a legitimate operation where we do everything by the book and we have a successful business to prove it", Ben Senes said.<ref name="ref1"/> The brothers have been in the business for 22 years. Selling jewellery and electronics is the "bread-and-butter" of their business but people also bring in highly unusual items. Through the years they have seen everything from monkey testicles, to gold teeth fillings to rare collectibles such as a vintage red telephone box.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Molloy|first1=Shannon|title=From monkey testicles to gold tooth fillings, these are the weird things people try to pawn|url=http://www.perthnow.com.au/entertainment/television/from-monkey-testicles-to-gold-tooth-fillings-these-are-the-weird-things-people-try-to-pawn/story-fnhoh21a-1227441647844|accessdate=20 July 2015|work=Perth Now|date=14 July 2015}}</ref>

Although ''Happy Hockers'' operates 5 stores across Sydney, the series is filmed almost entirely at their [[Bondi Beach]] store.<ref name="ref1"/>

